What is a unit test?

  - see this post: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1383/what-is-unit-testing

What is JUnit?

  - JUnit is a popular unit testing framework that includes a rich API for assertions as well as support for test fixtures.

What are text fixtures?

  - A test fixture is a fixed state of objects used as a baseline for running tests. For example, a test fixture could drop and recreate an in-memory database to allow data access tests to work on a clean set of data after every test execution.
   
